What is this all about?
What is a variable, really? Variables are one of the first concepts we&rsquo;re introduced to when we&rsquo;re learning to code. But there is often a lot more to it than meets the eye. And so we are going to take a deeper look at variables to get a better perspective of what is happening when we use them.
Variables When we declare variables, we usually do something like this: int var = 7;
